title: For Sale/Trade:  D Technik Waffen Werks VZ 58 vz58 with Czech wood kit and extras cz
postcontent: Well, it pains me to do this but my recent buys are forcing me to make a choice. I'm selling my Waffen Werks built VZ. This was the same company (along with TGI) to build Czechpoint guns before they took operations in house. This gun is built on a D Technik receiver and a D Technik kit. It features the original issue, cold hammer forged chrome lined barrel, and patented push down plate on the carrier. A few very nice features on this rifle, it has the bayonet lug and muzzle brake! Features many of the early builds did not have. Like all VZ rifles, it features a last round bolt hold open and milled receiver. They come in a full pound lighter than a stamped AK! It operates via a short stroke gas piston and fires via striker. It is also done in a finish that is a closer representation of the original. This rifle is and was very innovative for the time, and is considered a gold standard for auto loading simi auto 7.62x39 rifles! As always with used guns, there are light handling marks around the knob on the carrier and a few other spots. The barrel is bright and shiny with very strong rifling. The bonus, it's been fitted with a rare Czech surplus wood kit! Not only that, but I'm including the original bever barf kit as well. The lower handguard on the bever barf has also been fitted with a Chris Stone heat shield. Still not happy, how about both bayonets! Heck why not toss in a side folder as well. It may be original surplus in used condition,  but it's a rare 59 two rivet variation, and works great! Still not satisfied? Fine, how about a side rail that you could mount (needs to be tapped still.) Basically everything pictured, except the bipod, is included in this sale!
